is no longer a valid part of the code.

+ `function printPdf()` gives you the url of the exported pdf, to obtain the pdf itself you need to use [UrlFetchApp][2]
+ `UrlFetchApp.fetch()` allows you toobtain the pdf file as a blob and directly incorporate the latter into the attachment - it is not necessary to save it first on your drive and then trash.

**This is a sample code that permits you to attach your sheet as pdf in landscape to your email:**

```lang:js
